f Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":60,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"When Thomas Walsingham was born in 1395, in Kent, England, his father, Alan Walsingham, was 20 and his mother, Mrs. Alan Walsingham, was 20. He married Margaret Bamme in 1415, in Gillingham, Kent, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. He died on 7 March 1456, in London, England, at the age of 61, and was buried in London, England."},"et":{"1395–7 March 1456":"1395–7. märts 1456","1395–1456":"1395–1456","1398–Female":"1398–Surnud","1398–1445":"1398–1445","1416–1468":"1416–1468","1420–1465":"1420–1465","1376–1412":"1376–1412","1376–1446":"1376–1446","1395":"1395","7 March 1456":"7. märts 1456","after 1412":"pärast 1412","1415":"1415","1446":"1446","1468":"1468","1445":"1445","1412":"1412","1456":"1456","1455":"1455","1465":"1465","about 1446":"umbes 1446","1376":"1376","1420":"1420","1398":"1398","about 1420":"umbes 1420","1416":"1416","Gillingham, Kent, England":"Gillingham, Kent, England","Little Walsingham, Norfolk, England":"Little Walsingham, Norfolk, England","Chislehurst, Kent, England":"Chislehurst, Kent, England","Kent, England